%h1 Get Aeolus

%p
  Aeolus packages are available for Fedora 14 x86_64 and RHEL 6.1 (RC or
  later).


%ul
  %li
    %b Install the
    <a href="#rhel61" title="Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.1 packages">Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.1 (RC or later)</a>
    packages

    %br
    %br

  %li
    %b Install the
    <a href="#fedora" title="Fedora 14 x86_64 packages">Fedora 14 x86_64</a>
    packages

%br

.section-grouping
  %h2(id="rhel61")
    Install the Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.1 x86_64 (RC or later) packages
  
  %h3 1. Add the Aeolus RHEL 6.1 yum repositories
  
  %p
    %pre
      :preserve
        $ sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/rhel-aeolus.repo \
        &nbsp;&nbsp; http://repos.fedorapeople.org/repos/aeolus/conductor/0.2.0/rhel-aeolus.repo

  %h3 2. Install the Aeolus packages

  %p
    %pre
      :preserve
        $ sudo yum install aeolus-conductor-daemons aeolus-conductor-doc imagefactory

  %p
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This will install Aeolus along with its
    dependencies on the RHEL 6.1 x86_64 (beta or later) system.

  %p
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
